value.value: Adult ascending neuron with bilateral VNC arbors (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It is a primary neuron of the 27X hemilineage (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It exits the VNC via the cervical connective (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It receives input in multiple regions and sends output to multiple regions (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). There are approximately 4 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the mesothoracic neuromere and prothoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg52

value.value: Adult descending neuron with its soma and brain arbors in the gnathal ganglion (Sturner et al., 2024). It enters the VNC via the cervical connective (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Within the VNC, it fasciculates with the dorsal lateral tract of dorsal cervical fasciculus and sends output to the leg neuropil (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is GABA (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 4 of these cells per organism (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024).
